<title>USA: PowerTel makes acquisition, to split stock.</title>
<headline>PowerTel makes acquisition, to split stock.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. 1997-01-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>PowerTel USA Inc said it signed a binding letter of intent to acquire various shares and assets from Theme Publishing and Communications Group for $4.0 million in cash, common stock and preferred shares.</p>
<p>Revenues for Theme were about $10.7 million for 1996 with net profit in the six percent range.</p>
<p>It also said it set a one-for-six reverse split of its class A common stock, effective January 31.</p>
